# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your actual values.

```env
# Firebase Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project_id.firebaseapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project_id.appspot.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id

# Recommended for most uses
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://your_username_here:your_password_here@your_host_here/your_db_name_here?sslmode=require # replace with your real credentials

# For uses requiring a connection without pgbouncer
DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED=postgresql://your_username_here:your_password_here@your_host_here/your_db_name_here?sslmode=require # replace with your real credentials

# Parameters for constructing your own connection string
PGHOST=your_host_here # replace
PGHOST_UNPOOLED=your_host_here # replace
PGUSER=your_username_here # replace
PGDATABASE=your_db_name_here # replace
PGPASSWORD=your_password_here # replace

# Parameters for Vercel Postgres Templates
POSTGRES_URL=postgresql://your_username_here:your_password_here@your_host_here/your_db_name_here?sslmode=require # replace
POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING=postgresql://your_username_here:your_password_here@your_host_here/your_db_name_here?sslmode=require # replace
POSTGRES_USER=your_username_here # replace
POSTGRES_HOST=your_host_here # replace
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=your_password_here # replace
POSTGRES_DATABASE=your_db_name_here # replace
POSTGRES_URL_NO_SSL=postgresql://your_username_here:your_password_here@your_host_here/your_db_name_here # replace
POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL=postgresql://your_username_here:your_password_here@your_host_here/your_db_name_here?connect_timeout=15&sslmode=require # replace

# Neon Auth environment variables for Next.js
# Neon Auth environment variables for Next.js
NEXT_PUBLIC_STACK_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_STACK_PUBLISHABLE_CLIENT_KEY=your_publishable_key_here
STACK_SECRET_SERVER_KEY=your_secret_server_key_here

# Stripe Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_key_here
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_key_here
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_your_webhook_secret_here

# API Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000/api
```

## How to Get These Values

### Firebase
1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/)
2. Select your project
3. Go to Project Settings → General
4. Scroll down to "Your apps" section
5. Copy the config values

### Neon Database
1. Go to [Neon Console](https://neon.tech/)
2. Create a new project
3. Copy the connection string from dashboard

### Stripe
1. Go to [Stripe Dashboard](https://dashboard.stripe.com/)
2. Get API keys from Developers → API keys
3. Get webhook secret from Developers → Webhooks
